s detailed shape is extremely informative both on\nparticle physics and on the astrophysics of galaxy formation in small halos.\nThese expectations will be tested via the Hubble Frontier Fields and with the\nadvent of the James Webb Space Telescope, which will enable probing the very\nfaint end of the galaxy luminosity function out to z~8-10.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 10 Aug 2015 07:20:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-09-16"}
